reviews.review_text: Interesting set list but Acoustic lead is incredible There is so much acoustic lead on many tracks  over their regular electric set it’s really an amazing experience, it creates this incredible tone and beautiful full sound. The set list is like a list of an entire night of B-side songs other than kicking off with Touch of Grey, ironically the set includes “the other one” an intentional “B-side” that’s a true classic and exceptionally done this night as well. This recording is really beautiful. The bass, acoustic soloing, and heavy drum beats are all swirling clearly over clear vocals. I only noticed that two tracks had a weird glitch. But otherwise the recording is absolute tops.
